  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "200 \u0b86\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb4\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8 : \u0b86\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b89\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b85\u0baa\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Deactivation of 200 Garment Factories: Risk of garment manufacturing opportunities going to other countries",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "About 200 small and medium-sized garment factories are inactive due to fuel shortages and power cuts.",
        "In addition, the United Garment Factories Forum states that there is a risk that the garment production opportunities available to Sri Lanka from abroad will go to other countries.",
        "Most of the major garment factories, including Cipetco and IOC. Felix Fernando, vice president of the United Garment Factories Forum, said small and medium-sized garment factories face enormous difficulties in obtaining fuel, despite being able to obtain fuel by paying dollars at gas stations.",
        "\u201cSmall and medium-sized garment factories often have a indirect impact on large-scale garment factories due to inadequate fuel availability.",
        "This is because large-scale garment factories supply a range of their garment products to small and medium-sized garment factories for production.",
        "Thus, if the small and medium garment factories are not able to deliver the products on time, they will have a major impact on the large garment factories.",
        "Due to the current crisis in the country, there is a risk of foreign production opportunities being diverted to other countries and steps are being taken to avoid them, \u201dhe said.",
        "Meanwhile, garment factory officials and employees are unable to get to work in their vehicles due to fuel shortages.",
        "As a result, garment factory owners say their operations have been severely affected.",
        "In view of this, the garment factory owners have made a special request to Cipetco to provide fuel for the transportation of their employees.",
        "Companies have to bear the extra cost as they have to get fuel to run the generators as the power is cut off."
      ],
